  "decision": "Accepted",
  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a published observational study tracking hemolysis outcomes across clinical perfusion records; the study is described throughout this package as providing rigorous, prospectively collected hemolysis measurements that closely parallel controlled-experiment conditions, and the assessment team treats the resulting ValidationResult as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for output comparison.",
